---
id: org.dxos.plugin.crx
name: CrxPlugin
version: 0.2.0
---

Coordinates with the `@dxos/composer-crx` browser extension. Owns both the
user-facing settings surface and the receiver bridge that materializes
incoming clippings as `Person`, `Organization`, or `Note` objects in the
active space. Also owns the render-proxy settings (absorbed from the retired
plugin-extension) that govern how other plugins may use the extension to
fetch and JS-render pages in a real browser tab.

The extension discovers this tab via `chrome.tabs.query` over a configured list
of URLs and delivers the payload as a same-origin `window` `CustomEvent`. The
extension owns the DOM picker and bridge sender; this plugin owns envelope
validation, clip → ECHO object mapping, and user feedback (toast).

## Extensions

The following extension dialects are used in this document.
Each extension is defined in the Appendix or resolved via its URI.

| Term   | URI                            |
|--------|--------------------------------|
| `type` | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`        |
| `feat` | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`        |
| `test` | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`        |

## Types

```mdl
type Settings
  desc: |
    User preferences that govern extension ↔ Composer coordination. Persisted
    via the app-framework settings store. All fields are optional; defaults
    are documented per field.
  fields:
    enabled?: boolean            # default: true. Master switch: when false, the
                                 # bridge ignores incoming clips.
    autoOpenAfterClip?: boolean  # default: false. Navigate to the created
                                 # object after a successful clip.
    renderProxyEnabled?: boolean  # default: true. Master switch: when false,
                                  # plugins use the edge HTTP proxy instead.
    renderTimeout?: number        # default: 20000. Max ms to wait for a render.
    renderActiveTab?: boolean     # default: false. Render in a focused tab.
    developerMode?: boolean       # default: false. Verbose logging / previews.
```

```mdl
type ClipKind
  supported: person | organization | note
  note: |
    At runtime, `Clip.kind` is modeled as `string` so new kinds can ship
    from the extension without breaking envelope decoding. The receiver
    accepts `person`, `organization`, and `note` only; any other value is
    rejected with `unsupportedKind`.
```

```mdl
type ClipSource
  fields:
    url: string
    title: string
    favicon?: string
    clippedAt: string           # ISO timestamp
```

```mdl
type ClipSelection
  fields:
    text: string                # innerText of the picked subtree
    html?: string               # outerHTML, possibly truncated
    htmlTruncated?: boolean
    rect?: { x: number, y: number, width: number, height: number }
```

```mdl
type ClipHints
  desc: |
    Cheap signals harvested from the whole page at pick time. MVP uses a subset
    (og:title, og:image) as fallbacks; a future agent stage may interpret all of them.
  fields:
    ogTitle?: string
    ogDescription?: string
    ogImage?: string
    jsonLd?: unknown[]
    h1?: string
    firstImage?: string
```

```mdl
type Clip
  desc: |
    The on-the-wire envelope is intentionally permissive so that older
    receivers can read newer versions just far enough to respond with
    `unsupportedVersion`. Version-specific validation runs after the
    envelope decode succeeds.
  fields:
    version: number             # runtime check: only 1 is supported
    kind: string                # runtime check against ClipKind.supported
    source: ClipSource
    selection: ClipSelection
    hints?: ClipHints
```

```mdl
type ClipAck
  fields:
    ok: boolean
    id?: string                 # ID of the created object when ok = true
    error?: string              # stable error code when ok = false
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Settings Capability

  req F-1.1:
    when: plugin is activated
    then: |
      a single `Settings` atom is registered under a plugin-scoped capability
      and contributed to `AppCapabilities.Settings` so the standard settings
      UI surfaces it.

  req F-1.2:
    when: another plugin reads the capability
    then: it receives the current Settings with defaults applied
```

```mdl
feat F-2: Settings Surface

  req F-2.1:
    when: the app-framework settings panel renders the CRX section
    then: |
      a form is shown with switches for `enabled` and `autoOpenAfterClip`,
      wired to the Settings atom and persisted on change.
```

```mdl
feat F-2b: Render-Proxy Settings
  desc: |
    Settings governing the extension's search render-proxy (page rendering for
    plugins that scrape client-rendered sites), absorbed from the retired
    plugin-extension. Includes a connection-test button that pings the
    extension over the page → content-script → background path.
  req:
    - The settings surface renders all merged fields plus a Test connection button.
    - The ping round-trip reports the extension's name and version on success.
```

```mdl
feat F-3: Clip Ingestion Listener

  req F-3.1:
    when: plugin is activated
    then: a single window event listener for `composer:clip` is registered

  req F-3.2:
    when: the page unloads or the plugin is disabled
    then: the listener is removed cleanly

  req F-3.3:
    when: any payload arrives
    then: a `composer:clip:ack` CustomEvent is dispatched on `window` carrying ClipAck
```

```mdl
feat F-4: Envelope Validation

  req F-4.1:
    when: a `composer:clip` event is received
    then: the `detail` is decoded against the Clip schema

  req F-4.2:
    when: the payload fails schema decoding
    then: ack is { ok: false, error: 'invalidPayload' } and no object is created

  req F-4.3:
    when: the payload has a version other than 1
    then: ack is { ok: false, error: 'unsupportedVersion' }
```

```mdl
feat F-5: Clip → Object Mapping

  req F-5.1:
    when: kind = 'person'
    then: |
      a Person is created with best-effort fields:
        fullName  ← hints.h1 ?? hints.ogTitle ?? firstLine(selection.text)
        image     ← hints.ogImage
        notes     ← selection.text (truncated to a reasonable size)
        urls      ← [{ label: source.title, value: source.url }]

  req F-5.2:
    when: kind = 'organization'
    then: |
      an Organization is created with best-effort fields:
        name        ← hints.ogTitle ?? hints.h1 ?? firstLine(selection.text)
        description ← hints.ogDescription
        image       ← hints.ogImage
        website     ← source.url

  req F-5.3:
    when: kind = 'note'
    then: |
      a Markdown document is created with a small prelude (title, source link,
      timestamp) followed by the picked subtree's rendered text.

  req F-5.4:
    when: there is no name/title candidate
    then: the object is still created; empty name is acceptable

  req F-5.5:
    when: kind is unknown (future kinds)
    then: ack is { ok: false, error: 'unsupportedKind' } and no object is created
```

```mdl
feat F-6: Space Resolution

  req F-6.1:
    when: the active space cannot be determined
    then: no object is created; ack is { ok: false, error: 'noSpace' }

  req F-6.2:
    when: the active space is resolved
    then: the object is added via SpaceOperation.AddObject with target = space.db
```

```mdl
feat F-7: User Feedback

  req F-7.1:
    when: an object is created successfully
    then: a success toast is shown naming the kind and (when present) its label

  req F-7.2:
    when: creation fails
    then: an error toast is shown with the stable error code
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: Settings atom registered
  given: plugin activated
  then:
    - the Settings capability is available via Capability.get
    - the default atom value is { enabled: true, autoOpenAfterClip: false }
      (applied through the schema's optional defaults)
```

```mdl
test T-2: Toggling enabled persists
  given: settings surface rendered
  when: user toggles the `enabled` switch off
  then: subsequent reads of the atom observe enabled === false
```

```mdl
test T-3: Valid person clip creates Person
  given: plugin active, a default space present
  when: window dispatches `composer:clip` with kind=person, hints.h1='Jane Doe'
  then:
    - a Person is created with fullName='Jane Doe'
    - an ack event carries { ok: true, id: <non-empty> }
    - a success toast is shown
```

```mdl
test T-4: Organization mapping falls back to og:title
  given: plugin active
  when: clip arrives with kind=organization, hints.ogTitle='DXOS', hints.h1 undefined
  then:
    - Organization.name === 'DXOS'
    - Organization.website === source.url
```

```mdl
test T-5: Invalid payload is rejected
  given: plugin active
  when: window dispatches `composer:clip` with a malformed detail (missing kind)
  then:
    - no object is created
    - ack is { ok: false, error: 'invalidPayload' }
```

```mdl
test T-6: Missing name is allowed
  given: plugin active
  when: clip arrives with kind=person and no hints and empty selection.text
  then:
    - a Person is created (empty fullName)
    - ack is { ok: true, id: <non-empty> }
```

```mdl
test T-7: Unsupported envelope version
  given: plugin active
  when: clip arrives with version=2
  then:
    - no object is created
    - ack is { ok: false, error: 'unsupportedVersion' }
```

